As already mentioned, this problem is similar to the fibonacci series. Though you&#39;re not limited to start with a single cow with zero calves. So I&#39;ve written this more general method: 
```java
private static int numCows(int years, int cows, int calves) {
    for (; 0 &lt; years--; cows += calves, calves = cows - calves);
    return cows;
}
```

Or in a more explanatory way:
```java
private static int numCows(int years, int cows, int calves) {
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; years; i++) {
        int t = cows;
        cows += calves;
        calves = t;
    }
    return cows;
}
```
Which may be called like this (assuming you want the cows in 5 years with a single starting cow and no calves):
```java
int cows = numCows(5, 1, 0);
```

